summary: honestly guys, commissions sometimes feel like work for sure, but if you come to me with a vision of what you want and you...
body:
honestly guys, commissions sometimes feel like work for sure, but if you come to me with a vision of what you want and you communicate to me the idea that you want me to bring to life, i have SO much fun with it and it always turns out better than if i get a really vague prompt 

artist LOVE when you give them details like the emotion, story, or vibe you want from a piece and it will guarantee a better result in the end. it’s so much more fun to tell a story or convey a clear characterisation than to just be handed a design and an outfit. if you know what you want, the artist will too!

summary: I drew Natcatcosplay and James Charles from their Instagrams. This is from a sketchbook that I’m not really working in anymore...
caption:
I drew Natcatcosplay and James Charles from their Instagrams. This is from a sketchbook that I’m not really working in anymore because it was for my portfolio. But I’m not going to submit that portfolio any time soon because I’m no longer interested in that summer art program. No tea no shade but they were really bad at communicating when things were supposed to happen and I’m not driving across my long ass state without a month of planning. I’ll probably try again next year. This summer I’m gonna lock myself in my room and do nothing but studies and practice.
Or at least that’s the plan…
